During a press briefing, White House Deputy Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre discussed several topics. She expressed condolences for the victims of a recent shooting in Texas and called for action on gun control. Jean-Pierre also highlighted the bilateral meeting between President Biden and President Ferdinand R. Marcos, Jr. of the Philippines, where they discussed business, investment, infrastructure, clean energy, education, and human rights cooperation. Additionally, she mentioned that President Biden declared May as Mental Health Awareness Month and outlined the administration's efforts to address mental health challenges. Jean-Pierre also addressed questions about Speaker McCarthy's visit to Israel, the failure of First Republic Bank, the debt ceiling, and the potential expansion of the Quad alliance.